## 1. Purpose and Scope

This document is the complete, agentic-development-ready software specification for the Soaring Heights Kennel Management System (KMS). It is written to be fully actionable by both human developers and AI coding agents without requiring additional clarification. Every design decision, business rule, data model, workflow, configuration structure, infrastructure requirement, and testing expectation is captured here.

The KMS is a web-based application deployed on a homestead LAN for internal staff use and owner self-service. It manages dog boarding reservations, scheduling, billing, PACFA compliance, and kennel operations.

---

## 2. Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology / Decision |
|---|---|
| Frontend | React (Node.js); builds to static files; served by existing Nginx instance on host. |
| Backend | Python with FastAPI; REST API; auto-generated Swagger/OpenAPI docs from docstrings. |
| Database | SQLite; stored exclusively in backend container; no direct frontend access. |
| API Communication | REST API between frontend and backend over internal Docker network. |
| Deployment | Docker Compose; two containers (frontend, backend); homestead LAN only; no internet exposure. |
| Web Server | Existing Nginx instance on R630 host; KMS added as new virtual host. Ports in 9100 range. |
| Authentication | Local auth; username/password managed via command line on backend server (shadow file style). No UI for user management. |
| API Documentation | FastAPI auto-generated Swagger from code docstrings. No separate spec document. |
| PDF Generation | Backend generates PDFs for receipts and reports. Logo and business info from config. |
| Email | SMTP; all credentials and settings config-driven. Auto-email is a config toggle. |
| Logging | Docker logging driver (stdout/stderr). No separate log volume. |
| Backups | Cron job inside backend container; daily at 1:15 AM; writes to mounted NAS volume; 30-day retention. |
| Build/Deploy | `build.sh` script at project root; handles npm build, Docker Compose build and up, Nginx reload. |
| Schema Migrations | Versioned SQL scripts in `/backend/migrations/`; applied automatically on startup; tracked in `schema_migrations` table. |
| Testing | Unit tests (functions, failure modes, security boundaries) plus Integration tests (full operational workflows). |
| Container Restart | `restart: always` on both containers. |

