## 4. Configuration Directory

All configuration files are located at `/config/` relative to the project root. All files use **JSON format**. Config files require root/sudo access to edit on the server. Changes take effect on next container startup.

### 4.1 Config File Inventory

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `business.json` | Business identity: name, address, phone, email, website, logo_path. |
| `kennels.json` | Kennel type definitions: type, sqft, features, count. System auto-provisions kennel records on startup. |
| `pricing.json` | Nightly rates by size class (xs, s, m, l, xl). Activity type prices. Read-only from UI. |
| `pacfa.json` | PACFA sqft requirements by size class and stay duration multipliers. Hard enforcement; no override. |
| `smtp.json` | SMTP server, port, username, password, from_address, use_tls. |
| `phases.json` | Phase window start times: morning_start, afternoon_start, evening_start, night_start. |
| `system.json` | auto_email_receipt (bool), pickup_overdue_threshold_hours (int), portal_link_expiry_days (int), backup_retention_days (int), backup_path (NAS mount path). |
| `ports.json` | frontend_port (9100), backend_port (9101). |

### 4.2 kennels.json Structure

Defines kennel types. The system auto-generates individual kennel records (K-01, K-02, etc.) sequentially across all types on startup. New kennels are provisioned automatically. Removed kennels trigger conflict detection before deactivation.

```json
{
  "kennel_types": [
    { "type": "Large", "sqft": 30, "features": "interior and exterior space", "count": 8 },
    { "type": "Small", "sqft": 10, "features": "interior only", "count": 10 }
  ]
}
```

### 4.3 pacfa.json Structure

Stores the PACFA-compliant sqft requirements per size class and stay duration multipliers. These values are **hard enforcement rules**. No staff override is permitted.

**Formula:** `(dog_length_inches + 6)^2 / 144 = required_sqft`

| Size Class | Est. Length (in) | Base Sqft (< 5 days) | 1.5x (5-30 days) | 2.0x (31-180 days) | 3.0x (181+ days) |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| XS (Toy) | 12 | 2.25 | 3.38 | 4.50 | 6.75 |
| S (Terrier) | 18 | 4.00 | 6.00 | 8.00 | 12.00 |
| M (Spaniel) | 24 | 6.25 | 9.38 | 12.50 | 18.75 |
| L (Retriever) | 30 | 9.00 | 13.50 | 18.00 | 27.00 |
| XL (Mastiff) | 36 | 12.25 | 18.38 | 24.50 | 36.75 |

**181+ day exception:** If a qualifying activity (Nature Walk or Play Yard) is scheduled **and confirmed** for every day of the stay, the 2.0x multiplier applies instead of 3.0x. If any day is missing confirmation, the full 3.0x applies for the entire stay. The system proactively alerts staff each Morning phase if the qualifying activity has not yet been confirmed for a 181+ day stay dog.

