## 8. User Interface

### 8.1 Navigation Bar

Persistent top navigation bar on all screens. Global search bar always visible.

| Nav Item | Primary Purpose |
|---|---|
| Calendar | Default landing screen after login. 10-day grid. Primary operational view. |
| Reservations | List, search, and manage all reservations. |
| Dogs | Dog inventory; search; profiles; vaccination records. |
| Owners | Owner directory; search; profiles; associated dogs. |
| Kennels | Kennel list; status; issue reports; hold management. |
| Reports | PACFA Compliance, Occupancy Rate, Revenue Summary, Upcoming Check-ins/Outs, Open Incidents and Issues. |
| Activities | UI-managed activity types list; add and deactivate types. |

### 8.2 Global Search

Single search bar in the navigation bar. Searches across all record types simultaneously. Results are priority-ranked:

1. **Active and pending stays** (currently checked in or upcoming reservations). Displayed first with kennel number and status badge.
2. **Historical stays and billing records.** Displayed second in a collapsible section.

All results are clickable and navigate directly to the relevant object detail (Reservation, Dog, Owner, Bill).

### 8.3 Calendar Grid (Primary Screen)

- **Layout:** Kennel rows x date columns. Each day subdivided into 4 phase columns (Morning, Afternoon, Evening, Night).
- **Row header per kennel:** Kennel number (K-07), size class (Large), sqft (30 sqft). Natural sort order by kennel number.
- **Default window:** 10 days, Sunday to Tuesday of the same week.
- **Navigation:** Previous and Next shift by 10-day blocks. Date picker for jumping to any Sunday.
- **Auto-refresh:** Hourly. Manual refresh button in grid header.
- **Cell content:** Owner last name in Assigned and Used cells.
- **Status colors:** Free = Green | Hold = Amber | Assigned = Blue | Used = Red/Orange
- **Pending indicators:** Assigned cells with dropoff today = pending check-in indicator. Used cells with pickup today = pending check-out indicator.
- **Tooltip on hover:** Dog name, owner last name, scheduled drop-off, scheduled pick-up, status.
- **Quick Add Schedule button:** Always visible in grid header.
- **Overdue pickup banner:** Persistent banner at top of grid. Stacks for multiple overdue dogs. Dismissible by staff.
- **Data loading:** Day-by-day; each day column fetched independently for fast initial render.

### 8.4 Cell Context Menu

Clicking any Assigned or Used kennel cell opens a context menu:

- View Reservation Details
- Check In *(active only if status is Assigned)*
- Check Out *(active only if status is Used)*
- View Dog Profile
- View Owner Profile
- Add Incident Report

Clicking a Free cell on a future date opens the New Reservation dialog with kennel and date pre-populated.

### 8.5 Error and Conflict Display

All errors and conflicts surface as **modal dialogs** requiring explicit staff acknowledgment. No auto-dismissing notifications. Severity communicated by modal color and icon:

- **Red:** Hard block. Cannot proceed.
- **Amber:** Warning requiring override confirmation. Checkbox required. Staff username logged.

### 8.6 Owner Self-Service Portal

Accessed via a **7-day one-time link** emailed by staff. No account creation or password required. A **Request New Link** button on the portal homepage sends a fresh 7-day link to the email on file.

**Portal capabilities:**
- View own dogs' profiles and vaccination records.
- View upcoming and past reservations.
- View Incident Reports marked `visible_to_owner = true`.
- Availability calendar: Free vs. Busy by size class and date. No other owner or dog data visible.
- Modify reservations (dates, times, activities) before check-in. All validation enforced. **No override capability.**
- Request cancellation (staff confirmation required to complete).
- Self-book new reservations. All validation enforced. **No override capability.**
- No document uploads. All record entry is staff-managed.

