## 11. Testing Strategy

Three test layers are required. All tests must pass before any build is considered production-ready.

### 11.1 Unit Tests

- Phase derivation: correct phase for all clock times including exact boundary minutes (06:00:00, 11:59:59, 12:00:00, etc.).
- Post-checkout hold: correct hold phase and next-available phase for all four checkout phases including Evening-to-Night edge case.
- PACFA sqft calculation: all size classes, all duration multipliers, multi-dog combined sqft, 181+ day exception with and without daily activity confirmation.
- Size class enforcement: all valid and invalid combinations.
- Billing math: line item totals, discount application, total_due, 14-day cycle generation.
- Pickup overdue alert: fires at exactly the configured threshold; does not fire before.
- Medical acknowledgment: check-in blocked without acknowledgment when status is not Healthy.
- Kennel config provisioning: new kennels provisioned; conflict detection on deactivation; auto-reassignment logic.
- **Failure mode tests:** Out-of-bounds inputs (negative prices, invalid dates, oversized strings, null required fields, invalid enum values).
- **Security tests:** SQL injection prevention on all string inputs; authorization bypass attempts; direct database access attempts from frontend; config file access without root.

### 11.2 Integration Tests

Integration tests follow complete operational workflows end-to-end from API call through database write and response.

- Full Quick Add Reservation flow: new owner, new dog, reservation creation, size validation, phase conflict detection.
- Check-in flow: medical acknowledgment; blocked by outstanding bill; blocked by open incidents.
- Check-out flow: healthy flag path; required narrative path; automatic hold applied; PDF receipt generated; bill marked paid.
- Cancellation flow: owner request; staff confirmation; kennel phases released.
- Multi-dog same-kennel assignment: PACFA validation pass and fail scenarios.
- Billing flow: line items generated; discount applied; 14-day cycle billing alert.
- Incident report: creation; block same-dog check-in; resolve; check-in unblocked.
- Issue report: creation; manual Hold; manual close; Hold lifted.
- Owner portal: one-time link access; availability view; reservation modification; cancellation request; self-booking.
- Override flows: phase conflict override logged; open-ended pickup override logged.
- PACFA 181+ day alert: fires at Morning phase when daily activity not confirmed.
- Kennel config provisioning: startup auto-provision; deactivation conflict detection; auto-reassignment.

